The paper deals with the problem of finding a minimum weight triangulation of a set of points on a plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm presented in the paper uses grids to partition the edges, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of a greedy heuristic, which is a common technique in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The proof strategy used in the paper involves bounding the approximation ratio, which is a topic in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper presents a polynomial-time algorithm, which is relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
